My favorite sushi spot for about 10 years now. Best part the quality has never changed, prices are reasonable, I have celebrated bdays and anniversaries there, truly feel like family. Everyone that we have brought with to dine also have made it their go-to Sushi spot.

The food is good.
Tried this place once with my friend and I am addicted since then. I like the excellent mood and delightful dishes and drinks. Highly recommended.
By far best customer service I have experienced at a restaurant.
Delicious sushi, wide variety of choices of rolls. Everything we tasted was great. Prices were average for sushi, being BYOB always helps. Was dimly lit and quiet, a good date spot.

My partner and I have been enjoying S@kura for the past five years as our neighborhood go-to spot. They have excellent sushi at a great price, the ambiance is casual and quirky and they always have really nice chill music playing. Highly recommend if you're looking for a great meal and an authentic atmosphere!

I adore this spot! They prepare sensational dishes, they have a nice menu, The chef in that restaurant is an expert, I love a lot trying all their food. The food is always fresh, the service towards the clients  is efficient. I often eat in this restaurant and I not even once was unsatisfied. Highly recommended.
This restaurant offers wonderful service as well as tasty menu. The best place around town. The food served quickly and the rates are fair. Highly recommended.
Dumplings and sushi were okay at best. Chicken wings were good.Given how many other great sushi places there are in the City, I don’t think I’ll be revisiting.

This place is certainly one of the coolest restaurants in the neighborhood. Always when I go there I am remarkably pleased. They keep their very high  level service and the topmost level of food  they offer. You surely will enjoy this this restaurant. Very  recommended.

Awesome place,great sushi,great service,and the atmosphere is great for a date.the chef was very polite and had great recommendations..me and my girl love it.
I really liked the food here, and for the price it was excellent. These are simple but high quality sushi. Every detail was completely homogeneous. Definitely come back and enjoy again.
Excellent Japanese Food

we walked in we didn't get a great vibe from the place. It was really hot and humid which is an interesting combination considering it's a sushi place.  I'm sure they're really well meaning and have a good intentions.  However after we sat down we made the decision to go somewhere else to eat.  There is only two other people in the restaurant.

Sushi is great fresh and good tasting but the wait for your drinks or appetizers—not worth it!!!  10 minutes for our drinks even a green tea ice tea and water.   I give it a two because of How this restaurant is organized and run. Don’t go there if you’re used to the Japanese fun experience of sitting at the bar and ordering from the sushi chef or either just sitting at the bar.   You can’t talk or order from the sushi chefs!!!!  This restaurant doesn’t understand how to serve people. The person that takes your order it’s not the same person that brings your order. If they get busy it’s chaos.  My order went to a different table because they just dropped it off without any questions so the people that sat at the table ate it without any questions   I had to actually walk to the front of the restaurant get up off of my seat —do that and say where is my salad she was busy taking orders that were coming in the door why wasn’t the manager doing that lazy person -pre-Madonna.  There’s a manager there that just walks around and asks people how they’re doing but he’s not helping the servers—-/that’s a pre-Madonna get rid of that person and redo the whole situation. Chef Ramsey would’ve Had a real problem with the operation  If someone else wasn’t going to be paying for my dinner I would’ve walked out 6:55 minutes past my order of a glass of wine and a glass of green tea iced tea that never got delivered until 10 minutes later
Fish is very fresh, prices are average and standard for the type of rolls. They’re open late which is a plus!

Some of the most well done sushi I’ve had. I’m from the east coast and have eaten sushi all over the country (including both coasts for the sushi snobs reading this) and the sushi here is very fresh and very flavorful (and also inventive?) My favorite is the p’dodo. I’ve also had the mini egg rolls-very light and crispy with a good, slightly spicy sauce. The house salad was very fresh with the typical Japanese house salad dressing. My boyfriend who is very very picky about food in general (especially sushi) loved this place even though we have completely different tastes. He liked the dragon roll best. He loves spicy food but also said that although this roll wasn’t the spiciest, the flavor was so so good that he’s get it again(never heard him say that before). He also really loved the spicy edamame (he gets edamame everywhere) and enjoyed the spicy miso soup.
Favorite place to pick up sushi in the area. The sushi is always fresh and people that work here are all very kind!
My fiancé does not like sushi restaurants but puts up with it since I love sushi! This restaurant is so far is favorite sushi restaurant!
Good place to go. I like it!
Great place, small cozy. Prefect date nite

This is a nice little neighborhood sushi spot. I come here more often than any other sushi place in the city. The quality is good, prices are reasonable, and staff are always friendly. There's outdoor seating in the summer as well.
Good food
Friendly staff, awesome poke, good miso
Fish was good quality in the sushi, but the texture was let down by the very firm rice. It's hard to appreciate the fish when the rice is so al dente.
The waiter could be a bit faster

One of the best places for a quick bite in Logan Square. Chef owner is Japanese/Mexican and the menu reflect the heritage. Not uptight and hipster centric like so many Logan Square restaurants, truly a gem of a find. BYOB, so it is easy on the wallet. Enjoy the food.

So this was a difficult review to leave because my fiancé and I were truly torn when we left. I’ll start with the fact that we enjoyed our meal. The food was amazing, the waiter was very relaxed and knew to give us space but was also attentive. The rolls were delicious and the wait time was minimal. However, with almost nobody else in the restaurant, we were finishing off our drinks before heading out, and all we could hear was the (what we assume) cook talking about pushing us out and we aren’t making them anymore money. The waiter who was very cool told him to be quiet and be nice, but the cook just kept going at it. Trust me, we got up and left. However, what a crappy way to wrap up what was otherwise a fantastic meal. We both agreed we would want the food again but we wouldn’t want to deal with that guy, and living 40 minutes away it was unlikely we’d would be ordering take out. It’s unfortunate but customers typically remember the beginning and end of their experience the most vividly, and this was definitely an negative end to our experience.

This is such a good place. It is BYOB. And the rolls are amazing. I had the Sexy Chic roll and the Nightelf roll both amazing.  My SO had the Unagi Don and it was really good also. I would definitely recommend this place and will be coming back.😍🤤

They have some excellent sushi. My friends couldn't stop talking about the Acapulco roll. They could stand to hang a ceiling light, though; if you're at a center table at night, it's actually kind of hard to read the menu, it's so dark.
Good place, though a little crammy.

The Godzilla roll, rainbow roll and shumai were all mediocre. Surprisingly, the sexy chic roll was delicious. The food was overpriced considering the quality. The server moved at a glacial speed and without a smile to be seen throughout the entire experience. Very disappointing considering I've wanted to dine here for a long time.

Super Amazing!!! One of my favorite dishes were the GODZILLA,KING KONG, and Chocolate Cake with Ice Cream! It's  a very calming place and I really enjoy how beautiful each dish looks! It will definelty be your favorite spot for Sushi 😊
Amazing sushi and fantastic service. I used to live just down the street and have been here several times. Fuji volcano is my favorite!
Food was absolutely excellent. What I would equate to your favorite dive bar in Sushi form.

It's not the prettiest of places but the sushi is always on point. I've been here over a dozen times, never a bad experience. Anything off their sashimi/nigiri menu is amaaaaaazing- I'm in love with their hamachi, hamachi toro, and spicy scallop. 😍 Godzilla roll, California roll and sweet potato rolls are out of this world.  You want a casual, quiet, place to enjoy the freshest of sushi, come here. You'll thank me later.
Good sushi and fast delivert
Not an expert of Sushi, staff Hugo was very patient and explained dishes. Made our experience one to remember. Definitely we will  come back! Fugi Volcano was my favorite.
Nice place, good sushi, cool lighting
Pretty cool place to hide out and grab some sushi; has a Chinatown vibe to it (the size, decor and layout).
Effordable and tasty sushi!
Always the freshest, coolest owners and staff possible
Alright food. Friendly and good service.

I don't normally rate my restaurant experience, but this place was a rare find, off the grid and sushi was on point. I like small, quiet & local (with great tunes🎶) We will definitely be back soon! Thank you!
Not really a fusion menu, good solid sushi menu. No liquor license.
Sushi is AMAZING! Prices are reasonable.

Good food at excellent prices!  We came here after trying to go to another nearby Japanese restaurant, that other place was crowded with waiting time of 1hr. We decided to come here and were gracefully pleased!
Loved it!! The tastes are really good!
What a meal to start out the new year amazing sushi Thankyou it's worth driving six hours away again!

We had a small delivery order, gyoza chicken, edamame, 3 maki (Godzilla, Philly, and King Kong) and a few pieces of sushi, unagi, hamachi and spicy kani. Everything was very fresh and good. The hamachi was just excellent, i mean it was like butter, it almost melted in our mouths. The other peices were very good as well. We want to go there and eat in, the food was great delivered, how much better would it be to eat there. Definitely loved it.

Terrible experience here. After paying a 150 dollar bill the manager threw on the lights and yelled at us to get out. He then threw a beer can at us as we left screaming down the street like a crazy person that he didn't need our business.  It was bizarre and insulting.  The food is sub par as well.  Horrible, worst experience in Chicago.

I was in the mood for some good sushi and the sushi bar across the street from me was completely out of the question (crazy owner who drives away customers check out the reviews).  This seemed like a good enough place to try out after I looked at the reviews. Ordered a couple Rainbow Rolls, octopus, salmon, etc. Food came rather quick. It was good, but most of it tasted like it had been in a refrigerator for a rather long time making them either chewy or tough. The sauce the threw in was a bonus and helped give me a better experience. At the time I ordered delivery it didn't state that they already threw in some sauce with the order so I ended up ordering extra sauce for no reason then dumped it all after I was done.  You get about 2-3 pieces of meat per order so it might seem pricey, but its good nonetheless. If I can't find a better sushi place this'll be my go to spot.

First time ever having sushi and it was indeed delicious.  Came with my gf (sushi semi expert) and we had the godzilla, and the first one with mango (lol) and some octopus and sashimi. And some chocolate cake (very moist) with ice cream for dessert,  yum. Overall very happy with my first round about :)

S@kura is right in my neighborhood and one of my favorite places to grab a quick sushi bite. My favorite roll there is the Crunchy Spicy Tuna Roll and I love the Godzilla. They have great special and great coupons after spending $25 and about $30. You can get a free rolls or free appetizers. They are very fast with getting the order out fast when you order to pick up!

I love S@kura! I live around the corner, so it's officially my go to place for comfort food. My go-to is the Godzilla and Mexicana roll (my favorite). It's a little but pricey sometimes, but I think it's totally worth it. Also, try not to order takeout on high traffic dates (like Valentine's Day), you might wait a little long for your food.
I love the fact that they play JPop music! The sushi is incredible!!
Very nice people. Food was ok.
